<subSubSection pageId="8" pageNumber="137" type="conservation">
<paragraph blockId="8.[1370,2581,290,998]" pageId="8" pageNumber="137">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1372,1721,763,796]" pageId="8" pageNumber="137">Status and Conservation.</emphasis>
Simons’s Mouse Opossum has not yet been assessed as a distinct species on The IUCN Red List. At the time of the last [IUCN assessment, Simons’s Mouse Opossum was included as a form of Robinson’s Mouse Opossum (
<taxonomicName authorityName="Bangs" authorityYear="1898" class="Mammalia" family="Didelphidae" genus="Marmosa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Didelphimorphia" pageId="8" pageNumber="137" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="robinsoni">Marmosa robinsoni</taxonomicName>
) but was not named or formally assessed as a subspecies. Conservation status of all opossumsis being reassessed by the IUCN New World Marsupial Specialists Group.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
